🧠 OS Concept 1: System Calls
1️⃣ Simple Idea

System Call =
👉 way for a program to request OS services

🧠 Real-World Analogy

You (user program) cannot directly access:

bank vault
government system

You must request through official channel

👉 That channel = system call

⚙️ Why It Exists

User programs cannot directly access hardware ❌
(OS protects system)

So they use:

👉 System calls

⚙️ Example

In C:

printf("Hello");

Internally:

write() → system call
⚙️ Types of System Calls
Process control  → create process
File management  → open, read, write
Device management
Memory management
🔗 Connection to Interrupts (Day 6)

System calls use:

👉 software interrupts

🎯 Placement Question

Q: What is a system call?

👉 Interface between user program and OS.

🧠 Memory Trick
